-- Canada's TMX names Lou Eccleston as its new CEO
-- By Alastair Sharp
-- Mon Sep 29, 2014 05:11PM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, Sept 29 (Reuters) - TMX Group Ltd <X.TO> named Lou Eccleston as its new chief executive officer, the Toronto Stock Exchange operator said on Monday, after a lengthy global search to replace retiring CEO Tom Kloet.

Eccleston previously worked at McGraw Hill Financial <MHFI.N>, Thomson Reuters Corp <TRI.TO> predecessor Thomson Financial, and Bloomberg LP.